releases.title: The Soundtrack Gallery
releases.notes:
Here's another fine collection of TV and radio tunes used in programmes, test card transmissions and radio intervals - this time from the vaults of the Sonoton Production Music Library in Munich.

From the Radio 2 archive there's Ed Stewart's afternoon show theme entitled "Don't Run Away".  There's also "Our Happy Song" which was used during the Monday Movie Quiz, presented by Ray Moore.  It was played as one of the music tags that would end a round of questions in a particular category.
This album is dedicated to David Allan, who sadly died on January 2012.  David chose the music played to accompany the BBC Television test card transmission during the 1960s and early 1970s. Some of those tracks feature in this compilation.

Release is housed in a cardboard sleeve with an all-black vinyl replica CD.

artists.name: Manfred Minnich
artists.profile: German trumpet player, composer, arranger and conductor, born 12.12.1923 in Fischbach, Quierschied.  He was founding member of the SR Dance Orchestra and its first leading conductor until 1964. After handing over the direction of the orchestra to [a3984783], he continued to work as an editor for the SR radio broadcast. He passed away 17.08.1985 in Fischbach, Quierschied.
